---
import StudyLayout from '../layouts/StudyLayout.astro';
---

<StudyLayout title="The Two-Axis Model">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="kicker">// META &middot; EXAM STRUCTURE</div>
    <h1>The Two-Axis Model</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The CCA-F exam organizes its coverage along two axes. Understanding how
      they relate is the difference between complete preparation and accidental
      gaps. This guide explains both axes, shows how they connect, and identifies
      which one should drive a study plan.
    </p>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <section>
      <h2>The Core Idea</h2>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>
          <strong class="cy">Axis 1: Domains</strong> are the <em>what</em>. Five
          weighted knowledge areas that define everything testable.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="lm">Axis 2: Scenarios</strong> are the <em>wrapper</em>.
          Six production contexts that questions arrive dressed in.
        </li>
        <li>
          The two axes are <strong>dependent</strong>: scenarios are delivery
          vehicles for domain questions, not a separate body of content.
        </li>
        <li>
          One axis is <strong class="cy">primary</strong> (domains) and one is
          <strong class="lm">presentational</strong> (scenarios).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ===== DIAGRAM 1: Two-axis overview ===== -->
      <figure class="diagram">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 760 360" role="img" aria-labelledby="d1-title d1-desc"
             xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <title id="d1-title">Two-axis overview</title>
          <desc id="d1-desc">
            Axis 1 lists five weighted domains. Axis 2 lists six production
            scenarios. An arrow from Axis 2 to Axis 1 shows scenarios draw their
            questions from the domains.
          </desc>
          <defs>
            <marker id="arrow-cy" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5"
                    markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" orient="auto-start-reverse">
              <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#19f0ff" />
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- Axis 1 container -->
          <rect x="20" y="20" width="380" height="320" rx="4"
                fill="#120a24" stroke="#2a1a4a" stroke-width="1" />
          <text x="210" y="48" text-anchor="middle"
                font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="20" fill="#19f0ff"
                letter-spacing="2">AXIS 1 &middot; DOMAINS (WHAT IS TESTED)</text>

          <!-- D1..D5 boxes -->
          <g font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#d7c9f5">
            <rect x="50" y="68"  width="320" height="42" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#ff2bd6" />
            <text x="68"  y="94">D1 &nbsp; Agentic Architecture</text>
            <text x="352" y="94" text-anchor="end" fill="#ffb627" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="18">27%</text>

            <rect x="50" y="118" width="320" height="42" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#2a1a4a" />
            <text x="68"  y="144">D2 &nbsp; Tool Design &amp; MCP</text>
            <text x="352" y="144" text-anchor="end" fill="#ffb627" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="18">18%</text>

            <rect x="50" y="168" width="320" height="42" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#2a1a4a" />
            <text x="68"  y="194">D3 &nbsp; Claude Code</text>
            <text x="352" y="194" text-anchor="end" fill="#ffb627" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="18">20%</text>

            <rect x="50" y="218" width="320" height="42" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#2a1a4a" />
            <text x="68"  y="244">D4 &nbsp; Prompt &amp; Structured Output</text>
            <text x="352" y="244" text-anchor="end" fill="#ffb627" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="18">20%</text>

            <rect x="50" y="268" width="320" height="42" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#2a1a4a" />
            <text x="68"  y="294">D5 &nbsp; Context &amp; Reliability</text>
            <text x="352" y="294" text-anchor="end" fill="#ffb627" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="18">15%</text>
          </g>

          <!-- Axis 2 container -->
          <rect x="460" y="120" width="280" height="120" rx="4"
                fill="#120a24" stroke="#2a1a4a" stroke-width="1" />
          <text x="600" y="148" text-anchor="middle"
                font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="20" fill="#9dff3c"
                letter-spacing="2">AXIS 2 &middot; SCENARIOS</text>
          <rect x="478" y="166" width="244" height="58" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#9dff3c" />
          <text x="600" y="192" text-anchor="middle"
                font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#d7c9f5">
            6 production scenarios
          </text>
          <text x="600" y="210" text-anchor="middle"
                font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" fill="#7e6fa8">
            (4 shown per attempt)
          </text>

          <!-- Arrow Axis 2 -> Axis 1 -->
          <path d="M460 180 L405 180" stroke="#19f0ff" stroke-width="2"
                fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-cy)" />
          <text x="432" y="172" text-anchor="middle"
                font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#19f0ff">
            draws from
          </text>
        </svg>
        <figcaption>The two axes, and the dependency between them.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <section>
      <h2>Axis 1: Domains</h2>
      <p>
        The five domains carry fixed weights that sum to 100%. Weight reflects
        how heavily each area is sampled.
      </p>
      <table class="data">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Domain</th><th>Title</th><th>Weight</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>1</td><td>Agentic Architecture &amp; Orchestration</td><td class="num">27%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2</td><td>Tool Design &amp; MCP Integration</td><td class="num">18%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3</td><td>Claude Code Configuration &amp; Workflows</td><td class="num">20%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>4</td><td>Prompt Engineering &amp; Structured Output</td><td class="num">20%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5</td><td>Context Management &amp; Reliability</td><td class="num">15%</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li><strong>Weights are the real budget.</strong> Domain 1 alone is more than a quarter of the score.</li>
        <li>Every testable fact lives in a domain. Nothing is testable that does not map to one of these five.</li>
        <li>Mastering all five domains covers the entire exam by definition.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <section>
      <h2>Axis 2: Scenarios</h2>
      <p>
        Six production scenarios exist. Each attempt presents four of them at
        random. Each scenario maps to a subset of domains.
      </p>
      <table class="data">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>#</th><th>Scenario</th><th>Domains Tested</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>1</td><td>Customer Support Resolution Agent</td><td class="num">1, 2, 5</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2</td><td>Code Generation with Claude Code</td><td class="num">3, 5</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3</td><td>Multi-Agent Research System</td><td class="num">1, 2, 5</td></tr>
          <tr><td>4</td><td>Developer Productivity with Claude</td><td class="num">1, 2, 3</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5</td><td>Claude Code for Continuous Integration</td><td class="num">3, 4</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6</td><td>Structured Data Extraction</td><td class="num">4, 5</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>A scenario adds no new testable material. It only supplies <em>context</em>: a system, a scale, a success metric.</li>
        <li>Coverage of any single scenario is not guaranteed (only 4 of 6 appear), but coverage of the domains underneath them is.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <section>
      <h2>How the Axes Connect</h2>
      <p>
        Every scenario decomposes into domain questions. The scenario is the
        story; the domains are the substance.
      </p>

      <!-- ===== DIAGRAM 2: Scenario decomposition ===== -->
      <figure class="diagram">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 760 420" role="img" aria-labelledby="d2-title d2-desc"
             xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <title id="d2-title">Scenario 1 decomposes into three domain questions</title>
          <desc id="d2-desc">
            Scenario 1, Customer Support Resolution Agent, splits into three
            example questions. Each question maps down to a specific domain.
          </desc>
          <defs>
            <marker id="arrow-lm" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5"
                    markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" orient="auto-start-reverse">
              <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9dff3c" />
            </marker>
            <marker id="arrow-mg" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5"
                    markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" orient="auto-start-reverse">
              <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#ff2bd6" />
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- Scenario at top -->
          <rect x="200" y="20" width="360" height="56" rx="4"
                fill="#120a24" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="1.5" />
          <text x="380" y="44" text-anchor="middle"
                font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="16" fill="#9dff3c"
                letter-spacing="2">SCENARIO 1</text>
          <text x="380" y="64" text-anchor="middle"
                font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#d7c9f5">
            Customer Support Resolution Agent
          </text>

          <!-- Three question boxes (text wrapped to 2 lines via tspan) -->
          <g font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" fill="#d7c9f5">
            <rect x="30" y="155" width="220" height="80" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#7e6fa8" />
            <text x="140" y="176" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7e6fa8" font-size="10">QUESTION 1</text>
            <text x="140" y="200" text-anchor="middle">
              <tspan x="140" dy="0">When does stop_reason</tspan>
              <tspan x="140" dy="16">end the loop?</tspan>
            </text>

            <rect x="270" y="155" width="220" height="80" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#7e6fa8" />
            <text x="380" y="176" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7e6fa8" font-size="10">QUESTION 2</text>
            <text x="380" y="200" text-anchor="middle">
              <tspan x="380" dy="0">How should the refund</tspan>
              <tspan x="380" dy="16">tool be described?</tspan>
            </text>

            <rect x="510" y="155" width="220" height="80" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#7e6fa8" />
            <text x="620" y="176" text-anchor="middle" fill="#7e6fa8" font-size="10">QUESTION 3</text>
            <text x="620" y="200" text-anchor="middle">
              <tspan x="620" dy="0">When does the agent</tspan>
              <tspan x="620" dy="16">escalate to a human?</tspan>
            </text>
          </g>

          <!-- Scenario -> Questions arrows -->
          <path d="M380 76 L140 153" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-lm)" />
          <path d="M380 76 L380 153" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-lm)" />
          <path d="M380 76 L620 153" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-lm)" />

          <!-- Domain boxes -->
          <g font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11">
            <rect x="30" y="320" width="220" height="60" fill="#120a24" stroke="#ff2bd6" stroke-width="1.5" />
            <text x="140" y="344" text-anchor="middle" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="16" fill="#ff2bd6" letter-spacing="2">D1</text>
            <text x="140" y="365" text-anchor="middle" fill="#d7c9f5">Agentic Architecture</text>

            <rect x="270" y="320" width="220" height="60" fill="#120a24" stroke="#ff2bd6" stroke-width="1.5" />
            <text x="380" y="344" text-anchor="middle" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="16" fill="#ff2bd6" letter-spacing="2">D2</text>
            <text x="380" y="365" text-anchor="middle" fill="#d7c9f5">Tool Design &amp; MCP</text>

            <rect x="510" y="320" width="220" height="60" fill="#120a24" stroke="#ff2bd6" stroke-width="1.5" />
            <text x="620" y="344" text-anchor="middle" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="16" fill="#ff2bd6" letter-spacing="2">D5</text>
            <text x="620" y="365" text-anchor="middle" fill="#d7c9f5">Context &amp; Reliability</text>
          </g>

          <!-- Question -> Domain arrows -->
          <path d="M140 235 L140 318" stroke="#ff2bd6" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-mg)" />
          <path d="M380 235 L380 318" stroke="#ff2bd6" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-mg)" />
          <path d="M620 235 L620 318" stroke="#ff2bd6" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-mg)" />

          <!-- "maps to" mid-labels -->
          <text x="155" y="282" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#ff2bd6">maps to</text>
          <text x="395" y="282" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#ff2bd6">maps to</text>
          <text x="635" y="282" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#ff2bd6">maps to</text>
        </svg>
        <figcaption>One scenario, three sample questions, three different domains.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h3>Worked Example</h3>
      <p>
        The same domain concept appears across different scenarios, just
        re-skinned:
      </p>
      <table class="data">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Domain Concept (D1, agentic loop)</th>
            <th>Scenario 1 Skin</th>
            <th>Scenario 3 Skin</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Loop terminates on <code>stop_reason == "end_turn"</code></td>
            <td>Support agent finishes resolving a billing dispute</td>
            <td>Research coordinator finishes aggregating subagent findings</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Loop continues on <code>stop_reason == "tool_use"</code></td>
            <td>Agent calls <code>lookup_order</code> then reasons again</td>
            <td>Coordinator calls a subagent then reasons again</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="callout">
        The tested fact is identical. Only the wrapper changes. This is why the
        scenario is presentational and the domain is primary.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <section>
      <h2>Why Domains Are the Primary Axis</h2>
      <p>
        The relationship between the axes is asymmetric. That asymmetry decides
        where study effort belongs.
      </p>

      <!-- ===== DIAGRAM 3: Asymmetric mastery ===== -->
      <figure class="diagram">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 760 280" role="img" aria-labelledby="d3-title d3-desc"
             xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <title id="d3-title">Asymmetric mastery</title>
          <desc id="d3-desc">
            Mastering all five domains covers all six scenarios automatically
            (green). Drilling all six scenarios may still miss thin but tested
            subdomains (red, dotted).
          </desc>
          <defs>
            <marker id="arrow-good" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5"
                    markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" orient="auto-start-reverse">
              <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9dff3c" />
            </marker>
            <marker id="arrow-bad" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5"
                    markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" orient="auto-start-reverse">
              <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#ff3b6b" />
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- Top: good path -->
          <g font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#d7c9f5">
            <rect x="30"  y="40" width="260" height="60" rx="4"
                  fill="#120a24" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="1.5" />
            <text x="160" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="14" fill="#9dff3c" letter-spacing="2">DOMAINS UP</text>
            <text x="160" y="86" text-anchor="middle">Master all 5 domains</text>

            <path d="M290 70 L470 70" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-good)" />
            <text x="380" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" fill="#9dff3c">covers</text>

            <rect x="470" y="40" width="260" height="60" rx="4"
                  fill="#120a24" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="1.5" />
            <text x="600" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="14" fill="#9dff3c" letter-spacing="2">SCENARIOS COVERED</text>
            <text x="600" y="86" text-anchor="middle">All 6 scenarios, automatically</text>
          </g>

          <!-- Divider -->
          <line x1="30" y1="140" x2="730" y2="140" stroke="#2a1a4a" stroke-dasharray="3 4" />

          <!-- Bottom: risky path -->
          <g font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#d7c9f5">
            <rect x="30"  y="180" width="260" height="60" rx="4"
                  fill="#120a24" stroke="#ff3b6b" stroke-width="1.5" />
            <text x="160" y="204" text-anchor="middle" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="14" fill="#ff3b6b" letter-spacing="2">SCENARIOS UP</text>
            <text x="160" y="226" text-anchor="middle">Drill all 6 scenarios</text>

            <path d="M290 210 L470 210" stroke="#ff3b6b" stroke-width="2"
                  stroke-dasharray="6 4" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arrow-bad)" />
            <text x="380" y="200" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" fill="#ff3b6b">may miss</text>

            <rect x="470" y="180" width="260" height="60" rx="4"
                  fill="#120a24" stroke="#ff3b6b" stroke-width="1.5" />
            <text x="600" y="204" text-anchor="middle" font-family="VT323, monospace" font-size="14" fill="#ff3b6b" letter-spacing="2">GAPS</text>
            <text x="600" y="226" text-anchor="middle">Thin-but-tested subdomains</text>
          </g>
        </svg>
        <figcaption>Mastering domains is a superset of drilling scenarios.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>
          <strong class="lm">Domains up, scenarios covered.</strong> Full domain
          mastery guarantees every scenario is handled, because scenarios
          contain nothing outside the domains.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong class="dg">Scenarios up, domains not guaranteed.</strong>
          Drilling scenarios alone can leave gaps, because a scenario may
          exercise only part of a domain. A subdomain that no listed scenario
          emphasizes can still be tested.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Weight follows domains, not scenarios.</strong> Scoring
          samples by domain weight. There is no per-scenario weight to optimize
          against.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <section>
      <h2>Practical Takeaway</h2>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>
          <strong>Anchor the study plan on domains.</strong> Use the five
          weights as the coverage map. Confirm every subdomain is covered
          before considering the plan complete.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Use scenarios as practice contexts, not as a checklist.</strong>
          They are excellent for rehearsing applied judgment, but they are not
          a substitute for systematic domain coverage.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Watch for the trap.</strong> Treating scenarios as an
          independent content axis leads to over-studying the wrappers and
          under-covering thin subdomains that still carry points.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <section>
      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <ul class="bullets">
        <li>Two axes: domains (what is tested) and scenarios (the wrapper).</li>
        <li>They are dependent: scenarios draw their questions entirely from domains.</li>
        <li>Domains are primary and weighted; scenarios are presentational and unweighted.</li>
        <li>Plan by domain for guaranteed coverage; drill by scenario for applied rehearsal.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="foot">end of brief<span class="blink"></span></div>
    </section>
  </div>
</StudyLayout>

<style>
  .wrap { padding-top: 60px; }

  .kicker {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--neon-cyan);
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(25, 240, 255, 0.6);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    color: var(--neon-lime);
    text-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(157, 255, 60, 0.6), 3px 3px 0 rgba(25, 240, 255, 0.3);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .lead {
    margin: 18px 0 36px;
    max-width: 760px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  section { margin-bottom: 44px; }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    color: var(--neon-cyan);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(25, 240, 255, 0.4);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--panel-line);
    padding-bottom: 6px;
  }
  h3 {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--neon-amber);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    margin: 24px 0 10px;
  }
  p { color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }

  .bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 12px 0 4px;
  }
  .bullets li {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 6px 0 6px 22px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .bullets li::before {
    content: '▸';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--neon-cyan);
  }
  .bullets strong { color: var(--text); }
  .bullets em     { color: var(--text); font-style: italic; }
  .cy { color: var(--neon-cyan); }
  .lm { color: var(--neon-lime); }
  .dg { color: var(--danger); }

  /* tables */
  .data {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 14px 0 18px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .data th, .data td {
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-line);
    padding: 8px 12px;
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .data thead th {
    background: var(--panel);
    color: var(--neon-cyan);
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .data tbody td { color: var(--text); }
  .data tbody td.num {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    color: var(--neon-amber);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    text-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(255, 182, 39, 0.35);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .data code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    background: rgba(255, 43, 214, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 43, 214, 0.25);
    color: var(--neon-magenta);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }

  /* diagrams */
  .diagram {
    margin: 18px 0 8px;
    padding: 16px;
